Introduction To Information Technology

Axole

LECTURER: MR. NGUYEN MINH LONG

1. Dien Ma 

 

 

Figure x: Dien Ma’s SWOT reflection  

 

During our journey in Introduction to Information Technology class, I collaborated with one of the best teammates who I have ever had at RMIT university. In this class, I have studied many useful skills from My, I have study too much from her about writing report skill which is my weakness. Besides, My have an excellent project management skill, she has assigned task for everyone in every week and try to make the delivery of this project can be on time. I have collaborated with Thanh in 4 classes, so communication and teamwork with him is not a problem with me, He is a responsible and talented teammate. Although this is the first semester when I have formed a team with Tam, working with him gives me many opportunities to improve my knowledge both soft and hard skills. In this project, I have a responsibility to develop the website for our project in front end and design the UI for this webpage as i have familiar with the basic HTML, CSS and JAVASCRIPT. In our journey in Introduction to Information Technology class, I have studied more about presentation skills from my teammate, we have the mock presentation in the date before the real presentation. Besides that, This is only the second semester of me in RMIT and writing report is not my strength when compared to my technical skills. Our leader, My spent many time on reading our report and give me some feedback based on her experience in RMIT to have the report with the high quality.  

2. Thanh Nguyen 

 

Figure x: Thanh Nguyen’s SWOT reflection  

During the 11 weeks that we had spent together, we had concluded that only unity would instruct us to overcome the barriers. The drafting of our report was a source of concern for us, since Tam, Dien, and I are not writing experts. However, till My became a member of our group, our report had advanced to the next level, where it is clearer, more comprehensive, and more technically sound. We are really grateful to Dien and Tam for their contributions to our team's technological capabilities. Dien is regarded as a web specialist, while Tam has a foundational understanding of web technologies such as HTML and CSS. As a result, we had no reason to be concerned when we assigned them technical duties such as web development or UI/UX design. I have said that I was taken aback by the concepts proposed for our project. The methods in which it works is made and is used have blown my mind when I was writing and doing research for the project. Honestly, I have gained much more knowledge than I anticipated from our tasks. Before working on this project with my talented partners this semester, this will be the first time I have ever researched a sensor. Furthermore, developing writing skills, technically analytical skills, and technical thinking skills are three of the most important things I learned from this project. From the beginning until the finish of our project, the major of my work will be completed online using Teams, which implies that my activity traces on Github will be less than those of my peers. I wrote our report under the supervision of My, and she will be right there to assist me if I need any assistance. Finally, during my spare time, I studied and read extra books to better assist my team, more or less. Having Dien, Tam, and My as my partners for this semester is my great privilege. If I had the opportunity to choose any teammates, they would be the first people I would call on. 

 

3. My Nguyen 

 

Figure x: My Nguyen’s SWOT reflection  

What went well 

In this group assignment including the previous one, as the team have neither knowledge nor expertise in the field, I confronted challenges in term of planning the idea. Indeed, my idea in this assignment is quite risky for us to write down the report because my inefficient knowledge could lead to the infeasibility and impracticability of the concept or the technological unreadiness. To compound the problem, I was apprehensive when I did rough research and there are not many papers/ documents available regarding the technologies’ explanation. Yet, due to my determination for the idea of Axole, I decided to accept such risks to go on developing the system. It takes me quite a lot of time to deliver the idea to the team and signify how it could work by words. Although I assigned the tasks to team and they although their efforts are sustained, the writing parts of technological description and explanation in detail did not meet my expectation, I had to put fairly much endeavor to revise and modify the writing. This is not to say because of other teammates were not good enough or did not try hard rather it is due to my high expectation and the idea was originated by me. Thus, latter weeks I decided to do more on the writing of technologies while other supporting writing parts such as Risks, Group Process, etc. were assigned to other members. Furthermore, I had thought that we need to update the website from assignment 2 for the final submission of assignment 3. But it was not that until week 10, I realized that we must create a totally new website. Hence, latter weeks (from week 10 to week 12), I concentrated on writing the part left in the reports so that other three members can focus on setting up the website as quickly as possible. Then we just need to upload everything we have done on the website. Personally, I believe that this could optimize our working process and time. Regarding my contribution to the overall performance, I had serval strengths such as research, planning, report, preparing proposal, team management etc. (as listed in the above Figure) that results in the effective and efficient team performance. However, I am having weaknesses that could slow down the progress including the lack of hard skills, limited expert knowledge, etc. Additionally, I am not as good at HTML and CSS as other members, which could cause confusion for the group sometimes which I need to improve for future projects. In order to overcome this obstacle, I can conduct self-learning via online platform such as LinkedIn, and Coursera which are more professional and more academic compared to the entertainment channel like YouTube.  

What to improve 

Although I was a responsible leader, the project is not as efficient as I expected. Thus, in the future project, to maximize the progress, I will apply the following Urgent – Important Matrix (also known as The Eisenhower Matrix). By using this matrix, the tasks are done more efficiently while ensuring the critical priority of works. 

 

Figure x: The Eisenhower Matrix 

What I learned from teammates 

As s business student who led many student-host projects at University, I usually employ 5 phase of project management to lead the team. However, I learned a new framework to manage which is more appropriate and tailored for leading IT project. The method is called Agile Methodology and it is shared by one of my teammates – Tam. I found it very interesting as this methodology establish a detail guideline to monitor in each stage of the progress.  

 

4. Tam Kieu 

 

Figure x: Tam Kieu’s SWOT reflection 

During our working process, I believe that this is one of my best talented teammates since I enrolled in RMIT. All members have a willing to finish all the assignment as soon as possible with highest scores. Therefore, we schedule a daily meeting on every thursday morning. We never stop working until we finish the last assignment we must have, and as a rule, we almost complete every assignment before the deadlines 1-2 weeks. I complete all the tasks on time and attend in the website development process, where I learn very much from Dien. I learn how to use git better, create HTML and CSS components. I also learn how to write the report more professionally from My and Thanh, especially in the referrence part, I know how to follow stricly to the rules. But there is something that I want to do better. I learn many great animations from online tutorials to make a good-looking website, but I could not apply many of these to our team’s website. Also my writing parts have many mistakes and are not at a good quality, so I need many supports from Thanh and My, I’m really appriciate to what they have supported me. 

5. Group reflection 

What went well 

Overall, despite having not equal amount of task in quantity, we agree that all group members have input the similar significant effort into the project. Regarding communication, we kept close updates every week with each other that we did not miss any tasks. 

Firstly, our group includes talented members with their own mind-blowing ideas. Therefore, we came up with a good project idea which has not appeared popularly in the world and has a useful application in this Pandemic period. The suggestion is initially built by My - our Leader, she found a study biosensor tracking the Coronavirus after reading lots of reports. While discussing with the team, other members realized they could support My’s idea with data transmitting functions, Interface application. Then we together bring the idea into reality as close as possible, beginning with just a theory. Secondly, our team has a great task management plan at the early stage. The special thing about our plan is that we don’t have a break between assignments, and we always plan to finish the project 1-2 weeks before school’s deadlines. We also set a rehearsal day before the presentation and detailed scripts. Our team spends a lot of time with the website, in order to bring the best UI/UX into the viewer. Dien - member of the team uses his experience in front-end development to create a beautiful interface, it is designed with CSS, HTML and JavaScript.  

What to improve 

Although our team makes a great working process without any delay and controversy, there are things we could’ve done better. To strictly follow the time range, each member’s tasks are based on their strengths, so we lack chances to step out of the safety zone. Due to this, the improvement of each member is not as expected. Our team also lack bonding or sharing time, we do not have much time talking and sharing with each other their knowledge or feelings.
